   <note>Stilwell askes Eaton`s help in securing an appointment for his son as a mail route agent. He remarks on the Tennessee Legislature`s return to Eaton`s ideas on a public schoool system for Tennessee, including the need for a state superintendent. Stilwell comments on Eaton`s success in his federal position and adds that Grant must be re-elected to insure progress in "the Republic."</note>
